## Key Formulas

### Weighted Average Buy Price (Sales)
```python
past = purchase_df[
    (purchase_df['Article'] == product) & 
    (purchase_df['Date'] <= sale_date) &
    (purchase_df['No'] > 0)
]
if len(past) > 0:
    actual_prices = past['Price'] - past['Discount']
    buy_price = (past['No'] * actual_prices).sum() / past['No'].sum()
else:
    buy_price = sell_price * (1 - DEFAULT_MARGIN_PERCENT / 100)
```

### Date Conversion (Jalali → Gregorian)
```python
# For 1400.10.06
jdatetime.date(1400, 10, 6).togregorian().isoformat()  # → 2022-01-06
```

### Opening Stock Injection
```python
net_stock[product] = purchases + return_sales - sales - return_purchases
if net_stock[product] < 0:
    missing = abs(net_stock[product]) + OPENING_STOCK_BUFFER
    add purchase row with qty = missing, buy_price = estimated_cost
```

